{
  "texts": [
    "In line with previous literature that considers why and how to incorporate technological developments in qualitative research, we argue that developments in AI can advance qualitative research by augmenting (Do et al. 2022) the ability of qualitative researchers to conduct thorough, systematic, and transparent analyses (Chen et al. 2018) As described by Do et al. (2022:5):",
    "Equipped with this technology, a social scientist can produce results that are at the same time tailored to her needs and more accurate than what research assistants or microworkers could produce, while avoiding a potentially harmful division of labor.",
    "Using these models, she can become this \"augmented\" individual the pioneers of computer science dreamed about, a human person enhanced with (not replaced by) technology to achieve more (Engelbart, 1962).",
    "In the following pages, we model augmented qualitative research through an application of the large language model ChatGPT 1.",
    "We present practical guidelines for the use of this and other LLMs."
  ]
}